    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "For instance, I can set window options for a preview window using something like\r\n```\r\nautocmd BufWinEnter * if &previewwindow | setlocal wrap | endif\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there a flag set to id a floating window? I would like to be able to change the window's folding options to be different from those in my global config. Additionally, maybe set a default width by executing a `wincmd`?\r\n\r\nI've looked at #10081 - this addresses if the user is running nvim_open_win(); My particular case is when another plugin (coc) is opening the floating window with one of its functions (ShowHover or similar).",
